\r\nA fossiled egg of some kind.\r\n\r\nThe contents should be long\r\ndead, but mysteriously, it is\r\nslightly warm and occasionally\r\nappears to move.\r\n\r\nIt seems like it would break\r\nvery easily if handled roughly,\r\nso expert care is needed\r\nwhen examining it.
Skull of a Queen
A skull with small holes around\r\nboth temples and between the\r\neyebrows. It is estimated that\r\nthe skull belonged to a ruler\r\nof the ancient civilisation of\r\nEdenbar, as it is said that\r\nsoon after birth of a princess,\r\nsuch holes were made to attach\r\naccessories which would then\r\nnot be removed for the course\r\nof their lifetime.\r\nHowever, it seems that someone\r\nhas since stolen them, as the\r\naccessories are missing.
