The horn of the legendary\r\ndemonic beast Gerstein, said\r\nto be tens of times the size\r\nof human beings and attack\r\nvillages to devour them.\r\n\r\nThis beast, which almost always\r\nappears as the villain in fairy\r\ntales and folklore, is a symbol\r\nof evil, a status that remains\r\nunchanged to this day. It was\r\npreviously believed to be an\r\nimaginary creature, until now.
Old Jewellery Box
A very old jewellery box\r\nthat's worn with use.\r\n\r\nOne would assume that it\r\ncontains a mountain of\r\nexpensive gems, but the\r\nlid is locked and it's\r\nimpossible to peek inside.\r\n\r\nBecause the box itself has\r\ngreat historical value, it\r\ncan't be destroyed, making it\r\nsomething that amateurs are\r\nbetter off not handling.
Broken Music Box
A music box which plays a\r\nbeautiful tune when the\r\nspring attached to the side\r\nis wound up.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, the parts have\r\nrusted after being neglected\r\nfor so long that the spring\r\ncan no longer be turned.\r\n\r\nHowever, the jewels that\r\ndecorate the box have not\r\nlost their shine, and they\r\nalone will fetch a high price.
Meteor Droplet
\r\n\r\n\r\nA shooting star which fell to\r\nearth long ago. Its beautiful\r\nshine dazzles all who view it.\r\n\r\nThere are rumours that those\r\nwho obtain one will also acquire\r\nfortune and fame, though it's\r\nnever been proven.
Fine Urn
A splendid urn. It takes two\r\nhands to carry, and the design\r\netched around the exterior is\r\ncuriously mesmirising.\r\n\r\nIt can be found everywhere\r\nso doesn't have much value as\r\nan artefact, but it gives off\r\na sense of high-quality in\r\neverything from the way it was\r\nbaked to its tasteful shape.\r\n\r\nIncidentally, it's empty inside.
