Water that springs forth\r\nfrom a phantom floating island\r\nknown as Remies Island.\r\n\r\nIt's a mysterious water that\r\ninstantaneously heals wounds\r\nwhen sprinkled on the body,\r\nbut also has a horrifying\r\npotential to cause death by\r\noverstimulating the organs and\r\ncausing cells to be destroyed\r\nif even a small amount falls\r\ninto the mouth.
Ominous Chalice
A sacred chalice that, when\r\nleft alone, slowly fills up with\r\na jet-black liquid.\r\nIt is said that the nation of\r\nReville, under the rule of a\r\nhuge empire called Ragza during\r\nthe time of Edenbar, were made\r\nto create an ancient giant, and\r\nthe guilt of their people, who\r\nhad a hand in the destruction\r\nof the world, along with their\r\nunfading hatred of the Ragza\r\nEmpire, has turned into liquid\r\nand appeared.
Fortuitous Gold Coin
A small gold coin said to bring\r\nhappiness. The artwork of the\r\ncherubs and a shrine printed\r\non either side are full of a\r\nmysterious charm which\r\ncaptivate the viewer.\r\n\r\nIncidentally, the purpose of\r\nthis gold coin during the time\r\nof the ancient civilization was\r\njust that of an ordinary coin,\r\nbut it seems that it has become\r\nquite valuable now as few have\r\nsurvived.
Wish Fulfilling Jewel
A national treasure of the\r\nRagza Empire, who are said to\r\nhave had the power to take\r\ncontrol of nearly the entire\r\nworld during the ancient\r\nEdenbar era.\r\n\r\nIts shine has not dulled even\r\nafter a thousand years, and in\r\nfact seems to grow in intensity\r\nday by day. The light it emits\r\nis so bright that it makes your\r\neyes sore if you look at it for\r\ntoo long.
